The dollar dropped to a two-and-a-half year low as fast-tracked plans to roll out a coronavirus vaccine in the U.S. bolstered appetite for risk assets. The Bloomberg Dollar Spot Index fell as much as 0.2% to an April 2018 low after U.S. officials said vaccinations may start in less than three weeks. New Zealand’s dollar, the pound and the Norwegian krone led gains against the greenback in Asia trading Monday. Black Friday SpecialGet 15% discount on our annual subscription!
